headline: Nvidia lifts Nasdaq, Boeing China deliveries, Starbucks downgrade
summary: Yahoo Finance host Julie Hyman tracks today's top moving stocks and biggest market stories in this Market Minute. The Nasdaq Composite (^IXIC) is outperforming the market as Nvidia (NVDA) lifts the tech sector. Boeing (BA) stock is jumping after the CEO announced the company will resume deliveries to China next month. Starbucks (SBUX) stock is under pressure after it was downgraded to Hold from Buy by TD Cowen. Stay up to date on the latest market action, minute-by-minute, with Yahoo Finance's Market Minute.

headline: Starbucks Stock Drops on Downgrade as Analyst Cites Risks
summary: Wall Street’s expectations for  Starbucks  might be too optimistic, TD Cowen analyst Andrew Charles says.  Charles acknowledged the potential for CEO Brian Niccol, the former chief executive of  Chipotle Mexican Grill  to turn the chain around with a focus on operations and marketing.  In 2008 and 2020, two previous periods of economic turmoil, Starbucks underperformed other restaurants and fast-food companies, wrote Charles.
